Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  On motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed with prejudice.  Bail to be returned if applicable.

*Court ordered Defendant to pay Restitution in the amount of ONE THOUSAND SIX HUNDRED AND SIXTY-SEVEN DOLLARS ($1,667.00).  Restitution payable to DAVID HOBBS HONDA.  Court ordered Restitution converted to a Civil Judgment FORTHWITH and referred to Tax Intercept.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Hearing proceeded on the Record.  With agreement of parties, Court extends Deferred Prosecution Agreement to next court date.  Case adjourned for final review hearing in Branch 33.  Review hearing scheduled for September 13, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Review hearing proceeded on the Record.  Defense advised that Defendant has been employed for approximately ONE (1) YEAR.  Defense advised that Defendant has completed THIRTY (30) HOURS instead of the TEN (10) HOURS agreed upon.  No documentation has been received regarding restitution or Community Service.  Court went off the Record to allow Counsel to confer regarding Restitution.  Hearing continued on the Record.  Defendant will need to pay approximately a further FOUR HUNDRED SIXTY-EIGHT DOLLARS ($468.00) to prove a 'good faith effort'.  Court ordered matter adjourned to Br. 33 for Review.  Review hearing scheduled for July 11, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Defense advised that Defendant has paid a total of THREE HUNDRED SIXTY-FIVE DOLLARS ($365.00) towards restitution.  Half of the total restitution would be ONE THOUSAND TWO HUNDRED FIFTY DOLLARS ($1,250.00).  Defendant has not completed the total amount of Community Service agreed upon to in the contract.  Defendant is gainfully employed as of this hearing.  Court ordered matter adjourned to Br. 33 for Review.  Review hearing scheduled for April 11, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Katherine M Halopka-Ivery with student appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum  and Elements/Jury Instructions, received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 33.   By stipulation of the parties, restitution set in the amount of $2500.00 to David Hobbs Honda and the defendant has paid $265.00 already.  Review hearing scheduled for February 9, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Stipulated request for adjournment received and filed.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea/dpah in Branch 47  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for December 9, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Stipulated request for adjournment received and filed.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea/dpah in Branch 47  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for October 26, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Katherine Halopka-Ivery appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Branch 47 is in jury trial. Agreed Upon Request for a New Court Date is signed and filed. Defense needs discovery.  Case adjourned to Branch 47.  Status conference scheduled for September 29, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Court ordered case adjourned for pretrial conference in Branch 47. lr  Pre-trial conference scheduled for 09-15-2015 at 08:30 am.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with David Hobbs Honda.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Jessica Mckinlee Franklin in court.  Lucy Kronforst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Siefert, Branch 47.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant.  Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. 
Defendant was given a referral to the Public Defender's Office. Defendant MAY be Public Defender eligible. The case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Br. 47.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for July 27, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
